<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7965194>
    dc:description "FIGURE 40. Male genitalia of Siberian Sterrhinae.A–C—Idaea dohlmanni; D, E—possible hybrid I. dohlmanni × I.serpentata; F, G—I. serpentata; H–J—I. falckii; K–M—I. aureolaria; N–P—I. muricata. A, D, F, H, K, O—genital segment, ventral view; B, D, I, M, P—ditto, lateral view; C, E, G, J, L, N—phallos. Scale bar—1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7965194/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7965220>
    dc:description "FIGURE 50. Female genitalia of Siberian Sterrhinae. A—Idaea falckii; B—I. aureolaria; C—I. muricata; D—I. sylvestraria; E—I. pallidata; F—I. nitidata; G—I. biselata; H—I. aversata. Scale bar—1 mm." ;
